<subSubSection id="C3776556ED123876FC9AFE73FB59FDFC" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123876FC9AFE73FB59FDFC" blockId="579.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FC9AFE73FC25FE16" bold="true" box="[863,992,445,471]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of the new species is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FC2EFE2EFBDFFE38" box="[1003,1050,480,505]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">anis</emphasis>
(=unequal) and 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FB24FE11FAD4FE38" box="[1249,1297,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">clad</emphasis>
(=a branch), alluding to the extremely unequal sizes of the exopods and endopods of swimming legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED123870FC9AFD8BFEBBFA34" lastPageId="581" lastPageNumber="582" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123876FC9AFD8BFBA3FBFD" blockId="579.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FC9AFD8BFBA4FD9E" bold="true" box="[863,1121,581,607]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FB7AFD8BFAF0FD9E" box="[1215,1333,581,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389A</figureCitation>
) elongate, length 2.03 mm. Prosome curved dorsally, dorsoventrally depressed, gradually broadening posteriorly in dorsal and ventral view, unsegmented, but with several transverse wrinkles present dorsally. Cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FAE0FD03FA61FD26" box="[1317,1444,717,743]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389C</figureCitation>
) small, free margins rounded in dorsal view. Legs 1 and 2 positionedanteriorly on metasome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FB1EFCDFFA91FCEA" box="[1243,1364,785,811]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389D</figureCitation>
). Leg 3 positioned distant from leg 2, and leg 4 widely separated from leg 3 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FC6EFC9BFBE7FCAE" box="[939,1058,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389A</figureCitation>
). Fused third and fourth pedigerous somites forming brood pouch. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FAF5FCB9FA66FC50" box="[1328,1443,887,913]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389B</figureCitation>
) small, occupying 20% ofbodylength, 5-segmented, distinctly narrowing posteriorly. Genital somite short but broadest. Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FB85FC13FB74FC36" box="[1088,1201,989,1015]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389E</figureCitation>
) 1.5 timeslongerthan wide (60×40 μm), rounded distally; armedwith 5 small setae (1 lateral and 4 distal).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123876FC9AFB8AFA60FA37" blockId="579.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FC17FB8DFB80FB9C" box="[978,1093,1091,1117]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389F</figureCitation>
) small, longerthanwide, with nearly parallel lateral margins and rounded distal margin. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FC6AFB49FBE0FB60" box="[943,1061,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389G</figureCitation>
) small, 77 μmlong, 5-segmented; second segment subdivided by incomplete suture on one surface; armatureformula 2, 16, 3, 1, and 11+aesthetasc; allsetae naked.Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FBF8FB23FB6AFAC6" box="[1085,1199,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389H</figureCitation>
)slender, 4-segmented, consistingof coxa, basis, and 2-segmented endopod; coxa and basis unarmed; first endopodal segment longer than basis and armed with 1 seta on inner margin; distal endopodal segment slightly longer than first, 3.4 times longerthanwide (27×8 μm); armedwith 4 setae (2 minute setae at middle of inner margin, 1 subdistal, and 1 distal) plus slender terminal claw, 0.6 times as long as segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123876FC9AFA33FA51F835" blockId="579.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
Labrum missing. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FB63FA33FAD7F9D9" box="[1190,1298,1533,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389I</figureCitation>
) coxa with 4 teeth on medial margin of gnathobase, proximal 2 blunt and positioned close to each other: palp consisting of basis, exopod and 2-segmented endopod; basis lacking seta; exopodwith 4 setae (proximalmost slightlylonger than other 3); endopod incompletely articulated from basis and incompletely 2-segmented with 4 setaeon first segment and 6 setae on second; medial margin of first endopodal segment projecting. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FAEBF8C3FA66F8E9" box="[1326,1443,1805,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389J</figureCitation>
) bilobed; medial lobe (precoxal arthrite) with 1 naked and 4 plumose setae; outer lobe (palp) broader with 6 naked setae. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FC25F8BAFB9CF84F" box="[992,1113,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389K</figureCitation>
) short, broad, indistinctly 5- segmented; armedwith 3, 2, 1, 1, and 2 setaeonfirst to fifth segments, respectively. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FAE8F876FA61F813" box="[1325,1444,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 389" captionStartId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-21@580.[201,1385,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="580" captionText="FIGURE 389. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, dorsal; C, anterior part of prosome, dorsal; D, same, right; E, right caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B–D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 389L</figureCitation>
) lobate, bearing 7 naked setae and 1 broad, pinnate seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123870FC9AF832FDB9FB02" blockId="579.[810,1452,275,2070]" lastBlockId="581.[136,778,955,1220]" lastPageId="581" lastPageNumber="582" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
Legs 1–4 biramous (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED123876FB96F832FB7DF7D7" box="[1107,1208,2044,2070]" captionStart="FIGURE 390" captionStartId="581.[136,245,853,879]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,187,795]" captionTargetId="figure-19@581.[136,1451,182,811]" captionTargetPageId="581" captionText="FIGURE 390. Tubipedia anisocladia gen. et sp. nov., female. A, leg 1; B, leg 2; C, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592096/files/figure.png" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Fig. 390</figureCitation>
A-C), with endopods markedly smaller than exopods; protopod of leg 1 incompletely 2-segmented, but those of legs 2–4 unsegmented; first exopodal segment of all legs inflated. Leg 1 with large outer seta on basis; both rami 2- segmented. Legs 2–4 with 3-segmented exopods and 1- segmented endopods. Third exopodal segment of legs 2–4 tipped with small tube at tip. Leg 3 not differing from leg 2. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED153871FF4DF8BDFAD4F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592094" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592094/files/figure.png" pageId="580" pageNumber="581" startId="580.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[239,1341,209,1834]" targetPageId="580">
